This paper is about single image super resolution using a perceptual generative adversarial network. The main focus is on improving the quality of the reconstructed high resolution images by incorporating a robust perceptual loss based on the discriminator of the SRPGAN model. This topic falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of deep learning models such as convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and generative adversarial networks (GANs) suggests that the paper may also belong to sub-categories such as artificial intelligence (cs.AI), multimedia (cs.MM), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
